    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-05-20T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-05-20T07:00:00-05:00" n="346"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/5–2052: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DUNNJC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dunn</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d346fn1">Repeated to London and Bonn.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-05-20T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 20, 1952—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7169. Late last evening <persName corresp="#p_SCHUMANNM1">Maurice
                        Schumann</persName> informed me that discussion of <gloss target="#t_EDC1"
                        >EDC</gloss> in restricted French Cabinet mtg yesterday had not gone well at
                    all. <persName corresp="#p_PLEVENR1">Pleven</persName> was only Minister giving
                        <persName corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1">Robert Schuman</persName> real support.
                    There was considerable sentiment for postponing signature of <gloss
                        target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> treaty and contractual agreements. It was
                    decided to take question to full Cabinet mtg on Wed. Until then <persName
                        corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1">Schuman</persName> is not authorized to sign.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1">Schuman</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_PLEVENR1">Pleven</persName> had a particularly difficult time on
                    question of assistance France was receiving from other <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                        >NATO</gloss> nations to carry out effort in Indochina and at same time to
                    be in a position to contribute defense production and forces in Europe. Cabinet
                    wished to postpone beginning German production until size of cutbacks of present
                    French production program were known.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SCHUMANNM1">Maurice Schumann</persName> said he believed
                    Cabinet after very difficult discussion wld give <persName
                        corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1">Schuman</persName> authority to sign but he cld not
                    be certain until Wed. One thing I found disturbing in his account was apparent
                    extent to which <persName corresp="#p_PINAYA1">Pinay</persName> and other
                    Cabinet members considered <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> as complicating
                    factor in domestic program. We hear from various sources that <persName
                        corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1">Schuman</persName> is having difficult time in
                    Cabinet allegedly for following “too liberal” policy in <persName
                        corresp="#p_ALEXANDERTLHRLGA1">Tunis</persName>. Believe it more probable
                    that opposition to him arises primarily from his views on <gloss
                        target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> and Ger problem as whole with <persName
                        corresp="#p_ALEXANDERTLHRLGA1">Tunis</persName> merely an excuse.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DUNNJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dunn</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
